      <h2>What is Ceramic Coating?</h2>
      <p>Ceramic coating is a liquid polymer that chemically bonds with your vehicle's factory paint, creating a permanent or semi-permanent layer of protection. Unlike traditional wax or sealants that sit on top of the paint, ceramic coating becomes part of your car's surface, providing superior protection and shine.</p>

      <h3>Benefits of Ceramic Coating</h3>
      <div class="benefits-grid">
        <div class="benefit-card">
          <h4>Long-Lasting Protection</h4>
          <p>Lasts 2-5+ years compared to months with traditional wax</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-card">
          <h4>Hydrophobic Properties</h4>
          <p>Water beads and rolls off, making cleaning easier</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-card">
          <h4>UV Protection</h4>
          <p>Prevents oxidation and fading from sun exposure</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-card">
          <h4>Chemical Resistance</h4>
          <p>Protects against bird droppings, tree sap, and road salt</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-card">
          <h4>Enhanced Gloss</h4>
          <p>Adds depth and shine to your paint's appearance</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-card">
          <h4>Scratch Resistance</h4>
          <p>Adds a harder layer to help prevent light scratches</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

